===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|辰|虫|c1=p|c2=s|t2=insect|ls=psc}}.

May also be an {{liushu|ic|nocap=y}}, with {{zh-l|*辰}} possibly being an agricultural tool made from clam, see there for more.

===Etymology===
Possibly related to {{och-l|辰|5th [[earthly branch]]; dragon}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}); see there for more.

{{zh-ref|Carr (1990)}} organizes characters in the {{lang|zh|辰}} phonetic series into two groups, one of which is "dragon", which includes {{lang|zh|蜃}} as well as {{och-l|晨|id=1|dragon star}}.

